cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use this artifact in your research, please cite the
  associated MLArchSys 2027 workshop submission (currently under
  preparation) and/or this software repository.
title: >-
  Precision-Routing RVV Flash Attention: Compiler-Scheduled
  Custom Conversion Lanes for Edge LLM Inference
type: software
authors:
  - alias: noyaboy
    # TODO: replace with given-names / family-names + affiliation
    # before non-anonymous release / camera-ready submission.
license: BSD-3-Clause
repository-code: "https://github.com/noyaboy/precision-routing-rvv-fa"
url: "https://github.com/noyaboy/precision-routing-rvv-fa"
abstract: >-
  Open-source artifact for a co-designed mixed-precision fused
  flash-attention stack on the Berkeley Saturn RVV vector unit.
  Four RVV custom instructions on Saturn (vfconv.{nvfp4,bf16,fp8}.*
  + vfexp.v) with bit-exact RTL (57/57 ChiselTests) at 0.317 mm²
  standalone @ 16 nm. A gem5 5.1 RISC-V decoder + FU-latency patch
  issues all four customs natively. An Exo 2 @instr library +
  precision-routing scheduling pass lowers a high-level FA @proc
  to the fused decode-step kernel, running on gem5 at 1.21× the
  hand-coded reference (5.74 M cyc / 0.631 IPC at L2K, vs 4.76 M
  cyc / 1.366 IPC hand-coded). Verified 3.56× KV-cache
  DRAM-bandwidth reduction and 26-39 % per-row cycle speedup over a
  software-dequant mixed-precision baseline.
keywords:
  - "RISC-V"
  - "RVV"
  - "vector extension"
  - "large language models"
  - "LLM inference"
